  "prompt": "What is the process to get a brand name trademarked in India?",
  "response": "To trademark a brand name in India, follow these steps:\n\n1. Trademark Search\n- Conduct a comprehensive search in the trademark registry\n- Verify if the name is already registered or similar to existing trademarks\n- Use the online trademark database (TMR)\n\n2. Trademark Application\n- File an application with the Trademark Registry\n- Choose the appropriate trademark class(es)\n- Submit required documents:\n  - Applicant details\n  - Business registration certificate\n  - Logo/brand name design\n  - Identity proof\n  - Address proof\n\n3. Application Types\n- Regular trademark application\n- Use-based trademark application\n- Intent-to-use trademark application\n\n4. Filing Process\n- Online filing through the Trademark Registry website\n- Submit Form TM-A\n- Pay requisite government fees\n\n5. Examination\n- Trademark examiner reviews the application\n- Issues examination report\n- May raise objections if necessary\n\n6. Publication\n- Application published in Trademark Journal\n- Open for public opposition (4 months)\n\n7. Registration\n- If no opposition, trademark gets registered\n- Receive trademark certificate\n- Valid for 10 years\n- Can be renewed indefinitely\n\nRecommended to consult a trademark attorney for smooth processing.",
